    <section id="id1169754525104">
      <title>Chassis numbering</title>
      <para id="id4322959">The initial batches of the Lotus Seven S4 were built by Lotus Components and started with the chassis number S4/2650. Subsequent to the winding down of Lotus Components, the cars were built by the main Lotus Cars factory. Left hand drive cars were given the prefix <emphasis effect="italics">LBS4</emphasis> or <emphasis effect="italics">LS4</emphasis>. The total number is uncertain since there appears to be a gap in the chassis numbering between 3238 and 3299.  Upon transfer of production to Caterham cars thirty seven cars were built; however, Caterham assembled most of these from Lotus leftover cars rather than new manufacturing. 
</para></section>
